      "writtenOn": "2020-11-25T17:55:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "ah, no, that\u0027s not what I meant, but I can see how this can be confusing.\nMust here is a proposed prefix for the panicking version of the function, similar to: https://godoc.org/text/template#Must\nwe also use MustFoo in resultdb code: https://source.chromium.org/search?q\u003dMust%5Cw%2B%5C(%20f:resultdb\u0026sq\u003d\nand the mask package itself uses it too: https://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/common/proto/mask#MustFromReadMask\n\nI meant MustIncludes, not MustInclude, but this is still somewhat confusing. Ideas about a better name?",
