      "message": "sorry, somehow I thought buildMask is based on the reading mask.\n\nI think my confusion stems from the fact that we propagate both buildMask and updatePaths. Why do we need both? e.g. updatePaths.Has(\"build.status\") could be replaced with buildMask.MustIncludes(\"status\")?",
