      "writtenOn": "2020-11-25T18:25:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It was because I worried about * in the expression.\n\nI actually asked the same question to myself when I looked at https://crrev.com/c/1539264, and I thought that \"build.status\" must be explicitly specified, not via wildcard matching.\n\nIIUC, FieldMask.Includes() returns IncludeEntirely, if the mask expression is empty. Therefore, if update_paths is None, the field mask will match with all, and it\u0027s the existing behaviour of UpdatePath().\n\nI actually have the same pattern of code for \"steps\" and \"outputs\" in my child CL. \nQ. Should this code consider that the requester is attempting to update the status\n(1) if req.update_paths is None\n(2) if req.update_paths has \"*.status\"?\n\nMy child CL al uses update_paths for steps and outputs. I guess the same rule applies to all.",
